# Laravel Project Structure

This is a Laravel 11 application for DaleHurley.com, a personal website showcasing AI-driven tech entrepreneurship and banking innovation.

## Key Directories

-   `app/Models/` - Eloquent models (currently just User.php)
-   `app/Http/Controllers/` - Web controllers
-   `app/Providers/` - Service providers including FolioServiceProvider for Laravel Folio
-   `resources/views/` - Blade templates and pages
    -   `resources/views/pages/` - Laravel Folio pages (auto-routed)
    -   `resources/views/components/` - Reusable Blade components
-   `routes/web.php` - Traditional web routes (fallback to Folio)
-   `public/` - Public assets and entry point

## Laravel Folio Setup

This project uses [Laravel Folio](https://laravel.com/docs/folio) for automatic page-based routing:

-   Pages in `resources/views/pages/` are automatically routed
-   File structure maps to URL structure
-   No manual route definitions needed for pages

## Key Configuration Files

-   [config/app.php](mdc:config/app.php) - Application configuration
-   [vite.config.js](mdc:vite.config.js) - Vite build configuration for assets
-   [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) - Tailwind CSS configuration
